p: The 3-D binding orientations and interaction plots are shown in Figures 7, 8. While the binding energy data and list of interacting residues are shown in Table 8. Tocopherol, phytol, thymol, Falcarinol and linolenic acid form hydrogen bond interactions with the residues present in the catalytic triad (Asp214, Glu276, and Asp349). A number of active constituents' form π-π stacking with key amino acid residues; Phe157, Phe177, Phe300 ( Table 8) (Nadeem et al., 2019, 2020a, b; Farooq et al., 2020). Tocopherol has shown the most stable ligand-enzyme complex with the binding energy −7.7008 kcal/mol. While, phytol and linolenic acid also showed the lowest binding energy (−7.0629 and −7.01746 kcal/mol, Table 8).
